			P O J O  C L A S S
		 ( PLAIN OLD JAVA OBJECT )
		 
RULES:
	1. Class must be public
	2. variable must be private
	3. must having public default constructor. - mandatory
	4. can have args constructor.
	5. every property/field/variable have public getter and setter method...
	
ADVANTAGES:
	1. It Increase the readability and re-usability of a program 
	2. easy to write and understand
	
	
> getter method mean's a 'accessor' ---->> Update a value of a variable.
> setter method mean's a 'mutator'  ---->> Read value of a variable.